work, and I can't answer.

11:56.730 --> 11:58.240
It's embarrassing.

11:58.280 --> 11:59.850
Work is work. It's fine.

11:59.860 --> 12:03.130
Well, your sister works hard.
She comes by every sunday.

12:03.140 --> 12:05.020
- Yeah, I know.
- Don't take a tone.

12:05.030 --> 12:06.900
I'm not taking a tone.

12:09.010 --> 12:10.850
Look, I don't want to fight, ellie.

12:10.890 --> 12:12.170
I'm just worried about you.

12:12.200 --> 12:15.230
Mom, why don't we talk about this at
breakfast? 'Cause I'm going to be late.

12:15.240 --> 12:19.700
- Ellen, look at me.
- What? I'm fine.

12:22.390 --> 12:24.800
David was your best friend.

12:24.810 --> 12:26.930
How can you be fine without him?

12:26.970 --> 12:28.240
I mean, who do you confide in now?

12:28.280 --> 12:30.940
Because you're certainly not
sharing with your father and me.

12:30.980 --> 12:35.020
I... I... I go to counseling sometimes.

12:35.520 --> 12:38.430
You think I don't understand you.

12:39.400 --> 12:42.970
Ever since you were a kid, everyone thought
you had the world in the palm of your hand.

12:43.000 --> 12:46.630
Smart, pretty. Straight a'S.

12:46.640 --> 12:51.270
But I could always see when you weren't
happy, when you were holding something inside.

12:51.280 --> 12:53.990
I can see that now.

12:57.700 --> 12:59.040
You wanted to see me?

12:59.070 --> 13:01.240
You were late again today.

13:01.280 --> 13:03.000
I know, I'm sorry. It
was breakfast with my mom.

13:03.010 --> 13:04.790
It's hard to get her to stop talking.

13:04.820 --> 13:08.320
Live your life on your
own time, not mine.

13:08.330 --> 13:11.450
It won't happen again. Anything else?

13:11.460 --> 13:14.400
Are you close to your mother?

13:17.420 --> 13:19.660
Not really.

13:19.710 --> 13:22.340
She has a hard time
understanding my life.

13:22.370 --> 13:25.550
Well, you can always talk to me, ellen.

13:26.270 --> 13:29.340
- Thanks, patty.
- Hold on a minute.

13:30.240 --> 13:33.220
Shut the door. Sit down.

13:42.170 --> 13:48.330
I know that michael likes talking
to you when he comes to the office.

13:49.580 --> 13:52.800
Yeah, we've chatted a few times.

13:52.830 --> 13:55.720
Has he mentioned his girlfriend?

13:56.250 --> 14:00.150
No. Never. Why?

14:00.760 --> 14:05.530
He'S... he's been so secretive.

14:06.450 --> 14:12.950
We're finally going to meet her, but I was
thinking, if he talked to you about her or...

14:12.980 --> 14:15.950
No, he hasn't mentioned her, but...

14:15.990 --> 14:19.870
I mean, he's a teenager. He's probably
more nervous about it than you are.

14:21.570 --> 14:24.430
When did you introduce
david to your parents?

14:24.460 --> 14:26.720
- Oh, that was easy.
- Why?

14:27.270 --> 14:31.450
He was premed, responsible, honest.

14:31.480 --> 14:34.430
Yeah, my parents were thrilled.

14:37.820 --> 14:40.820
I got to get back to work.

14:43.750 --> 14:49.370
So, what are we thinking?
Schizoid? Skinhead? Scientologist?

14:49.380 --> 14:53.800
Well, if she has piercings
or a tattoo, I'm walking out.

14:55.180 --> 15:00.080
Mom, phil... I'd like
you to meet jill burnham.

15:00.090 --> 15:02.200
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

15:02.210 --> 15:06.200
Michael's told me so much about you.
I'm so glad we could finally meet.

15:06.490 --> 15:09.100
It's my pleasure.

15:09.320 --> 15:12.250
Have a seat, please.

15:15.280 --> 15:17.400
This place was a great choice.

15:17.440 --> 15:19.600
I used to come here all the
time in my teaching days.

15:19.640 --> 15:22.620
Jill taught art history at columbia.

15:23.790 --> 15:26.320
And when was that?

15:26.350 --> 15:31.180
It was right after i got my
phd, so, uh... it was '88 to '92.

15:32.630 --> 15:34.950
You okay over by the window?

15:35.000 --> 15:38.500
- Jill's just getting over a cold.
- I'm fine. Thank you.

15:41.410 --> 15:44.350
So, how did you two meet?

15:44.380 --> 15:47.010
Jill owns a gallery in chelsea.

15:47.060 --> 15:49.450
Some really interesting work.

15:49.610 --> 15:52.300
You two should come
down and check it out.

15:52.360 --> 15:54.090
We'd love to.

15:54.120 --> 15:57.050
We still have that wall
to fill in the guest room.

16:06.080 --> 16:09.050
You know what I love on a
chilly night is a nice barolo.

16:09.080 --> 16:13.100
Excuse me. Could we have a
bottle of the '99 reserve?

16:13.110 --> 16:14.040
Four glasses.

16:14.050 --> 16:18.040
Absolutely not. You are 18.

16:22.650 --> 16:26.230
So, jill... do you have children?

16:33.980 --> 16:36.470
How has retirement been?

16:37.090 --> 16:38.900
Quiet.

16:38.960 --> 16:41.820
Quiet's good.

16:41.830 --> 16:43.640
Most of the time.

16:45.380 --> 16:49.990
Of course, it wouldn't be so
quiet if I had some grandchildren.

16:51.900 --> 16:56.680
You know, if you wanted grandkids, dad, you
should have had more than one kid yourself.

16:56.720 --> 17:00.190
It was a bad idea to put
all your eggs in one basket.

17:00.500 --> 17:02.610
Your mother didn't want any more.

17:02.650 --> 17:05.210
- That's 'cause she was depressed.
- That's nonsense.

17:05.220 --> 17:07.520
What do you know? You were
overseas most of the time.

17:07.530 --> 17:09.890
I knew her, claire.

17:09.920 --> 17:12.800
Don't try to tell me I didn't know her.

17:12.829 --> 17:15.920
Well, I had to live with her,
and she was depressed, because,

17:15.950 --> 17:19.589
instead of going out into the world and
accomplishing something, she had to raise me.

17:34.370 --> 17:37.630
I'm sorry you don't
have grandchildren, dad.

17:39.520 --> 17:41.820
I truly am.

17:41.870 --> 17:44.270
I guess there just wasn't enough time.

17:44.280 --> 17:45.380
Time?

17:45.440 --> 17:49.240
You know, the irony of this is that you're
the one who pushed me to go to law school.

17:49.280 --> 17:52.410
Time doesn't have anything to do with
it. Either you want kids or you don'T.

17:52.420 --> 17:56.650
I'm the lead counsel for one of the
biggest energy companies in the world.

17:56.690 --> 17:59.000
You know how many women can say that?

17:59.010 --> 18:01.530
One. Me.

18:04.470 --> 18:06.720
Yeah.

18:08.870 --> 18:12.650
But what do you have to
look forward to, claire?

18:18.260 --> 18:21.110
I have to get back to work.

18:21.380 --> 18:24.390
thank you for coming
in town for my party.

18:24.400 --> 18:25.620
You're leaving?

18:25.680 --> 18:30.090
Yes, dad, and please don't
have another glass of wine.

18:32.110 --> 18:34.990
See you, dad.

18:41.890 --> 18:44.460
Since when did you start smoking?

18:46.000 --> 18:49.320
Try getting a divorce.

18:51.800 --> 18:54.620
I answered your phone the other day.

18:54.750 --> 18:56.080
Why did you do that?

18:56.140 --> 18:59.160
Caller id said pam
werner was on the phone.

18:59.170 --> 19:01.870
