19:22.120 --> 19:24.850
She told me she was.

19:27.650 --> 19:29.970
Stop lying.

19:30.030 --> 19:32.990
Pam said she hadn't
spoken to you in months.

19:34.680 --> 19:38.180
Now, why don't you just tell
me what the hell is going on.

19:40.380 --> 19:43.140
Come on, randy.

19:43.170 --> 19:45.560
Don't give me that shit.

19:45.590 --> 19:48.370
Who was on the goddamned phone?

19:55.840 --> 19:58.950
I... I don't know his name.

19:59.610 --> 20:02.190
Is he from the bureau?

20:02.200 --> 20:07.400
Look, he'S... it's just some guy
who has an interest in our case.

20:07.410 --> 20:10.820
He wants patty hewes taken
down as badly as we do.

20:11.690 --> 20:13.170
What's your arrangement?

20:13.200 --> 20:15.710
From time to time, he...

20:15.740 --> 20:20.380
he pays me a little something just to let
him know where the investigation stands.

20:21.130 --> 20:25.920
I'm broke, randy. I have
alimony. I have child support.

20:26.550 --> 20:29.470
Okay, hang on, hang on, hang on.

20:30.950 --> 20:34.050
I'll talk to him. I'll
have him cut you in.

20:34.060 --> 20:37.330
All right, I'll get you
the same deal that I got.

20:39.160 --> 20:43.540
It's just more money to do
exactly what we're doing anyway.

20:44.330 --> 20:47.700
- He hasn't asked you for anything else?
- Nothing.

20:52.350 --> 20:56.160
Think about it. Please.

21:09.780 --> 21:12.680
I got some of the oolong
you like from mcnulty'S.

21:12.720 --> 21:15.130
No, thanks.

21:22.030 --> 21:24.960
Last night meant a lot to me.

21:28.350 --> 21:31.540
Of course, I was
surprised at first, but...

21:31.550 --> 21:35.970
I'm glad you felt comfortable
enough to introduce us to jill.

21:35.980 --> 21:39.990
She's become a big part of my life.

21:44.830 --> 21:50.430
When I was growing up, parents rarely had
that kind of relationship with their kids.

21:50.440 --> 21:52.930
My...

21:52.980 --> 21:55.380
I am sure my father would never...

21:55.400 --> 21:57.860
It was a different era.

21:59.330 --> 22:04.290
Well, I hope you know if there's anything
you want to share with me, I'm here.

22:04.300 --> 22:07.020
Thanks.

22:14.100 --> 22:17.330
This isn't the tea I like.

22:21.990 --> 22:25.390
I'm authorized to offer a settlement.

22:26.940 --> 22:28.580
Are you amenable?

22:28.640 --> 22:30.500
Throw out a number. We'll see.

22:30.510 --> 22:33.500
Oh, no, i don't work that
way. It's a waste of time.

22:33.510 --> 22:37.800
I offer a number, you reject it, you offer a
number, I reject it, and on and on and on and on.

22:37.830 --> 22:40.040
It's so boring.

22:40.090 --> 22:44.180
Well, no one says it has
to be boring. Surprise me.

22:44.190 --> 22:48.310
Let's talk about why you're
really trying this case.

22:48.760 --> 22:51.270
You don't care about
our wounded shareholders.

22:51.330 --> 22:54.650
I don't? What do you think I care about?

22:54.660 --> 22:57.030
Daniel purcell.

22:57.060 --> 23:02.170
He embarrassed you. He flipped
on the stand. You want revenge.

23:02.180 --> 23:04.360
My boss doesn't understand that.

23:04.420 --> 23:09.750
He thinks that you're motivated by greed
like the rest of the world, but I get it.

23:10.150 --> 23:15.010
I get revenge, so I know that you don't
want to settle no matter what the price.

23:15.060 --> 23:16.840
That's very astute.

23:16.880 --> 23:20.370
Good, because I don't
want to settle either.

23:20.410 --> 23:23.120
See you in court.

23:23.920 --> 23:26.650
Can I ask you a question?

23:26.660 --> 23:28.380
Please.

23:28.430 --> 23:32.720
Why were you defending a
hooker on a cocaine charge?

23:33.360 --> 23:35.420
Because she needed a lawyer.

23:35.430 --> 23:38.060
Why didn't finn garrety need a lawyer?

23:38.110 --> 23:42.180
Finn garrety? I don't
believe I know who that is.

23:42.930 --> 23:46.950
Well, mention that name to your boss,

23:46.960 --> 23:51.520
and whatever settlement figure he's
authorized, tell him to triple it.

23:54.040 --> 23:57.750
And we'll start boring
each other from there.

23:59.410 --> 24:01.630
So what happened with patty hewes?

24:01.680 --> 24:04.780
She told me to triple the offer.

24:06.360 --> 24:10.170
Don't bother countering.
She'll come back to us.

24:10.180 --> 24:14.530
No, walt, she's not going to settle.

24:16.900 --> 24:23.620
She asked me about the
prostitute that you had me defend.

24:23.630 --> 24:26.650
We have nothing to worry about.
She can't hurt me with that.

24:26.660 --> 24:30.330
Can she hurt you with finn garrety?

24:31.640 --> 24:34.480
Who is he, walt?

24:35.930 --> 24:38.850
No one important.

24:44.750 --> 24:48.210
It wasn't your prostitute, was it?

24:50.370 --> 24:52.100
you compromised me.

24:52.180 --> 24:55.010
You had me go into patty hewes'
office without all the facts.

24:55.050 --> 24:56.760
- Claire...
- No.

24:56.770 --> 24:59.370
I want to know what's going on.

24:59.380 --> 25:03.750
Otherwise I'll go right back to my office
and I will type up a letter of resignation.

25:03.780 --> 25:05.680
Take it easy, okay?

25:05.730 --> 25:07.390
Your father's in town; the
stress is getting to you.

25:07.450 --> 25:10.170
There's no reason to be paranoid.

25:13.240 --> 25:15.650
Tell me.

25:19.520 --> 25:21.030
Finn garrety is the son of a friend.

25:21.060 --> 25:24.000
He made a stupid mistake
and got himself into trouble.

25:24.020 --> 25:26.850
So you lied to me.

25:26.860 --> 25:29.620
I'm sorry, claire.

25:30.570 --> 25:34.040
I was just trying to protect a
friend. That's all there is to it.

25:47.660 --> 25:50.860
You have one new message.

25:50.870 --> 25:52.740
Hey, it's katie.

25:52.750 --> 25:56.600
You're probably alone in your
hotel, working or just going to bed.

25:56.630 --> 26:00.670
So why don't you come out for
a change? I'll buy you a drink.

26:07.590 --> 26:11.290
Ellen. I thought there was no
way that you were going to come.

26:11.300 --> 26:13.720
Well, here I am.

26:29.650 --> 26:32.050
The staring has got to stop.

26:32.060 --> 26:35.640
If you're going to look at me all
night, at least you can talk to me.

26:35.940 --> 26:39.730
do you have something to say
or are you just window-shopping?

26:39.740 --> 26:42.840
Um, I'm moving to
chicago in the morning.

26:42.860 --> 26:45.300
This is a big night for you, huh?

26:45.320 --> 26:47.770
Last night in new york-- you
want to make it memorable?

26:47.790 --> 26:48.960
Sure, why not?

26:49.010 --> 26:53.410
If I asked you back to
my hotel with me tonight,

26:53.420 --> 26:56.430
would that be something
that you might remember?

26:57.240 --> 26:59.210
Probably.

26:59.230 --> 27:02.300
This is what people do, right?

27:02.340 --> 27:07.130
They go out, they get
drunk, they hook up.

27:07.140 --> 27:11.790
So what do you say? Would
you like another round?

27:11.800 --> 27:14.030
Sure.

27:26.550 --> 27:30.620
Thank you for meeting me so late.

27:31.130 --> 27:33.520
You said you needed my help.

27:33.550 --> 27:39.650
A couple weeks ago, walter kendrick asks me
to defend a prostitute on cocaine charges.

27:41.730 --> 27:45.260
the john's name was finn garrety.

27:45.270 --> 27:46.440
I don't know that name.

27:46.480 --> 27:50.730
I did some research. Turns out
he's a big player on wall street.

27:50.740 --> 27:53.990
He trades energy futures.

27:57.090 --> 28:02.470
Since the merger...
I've been watching unr.

28:02.890 --> 28:04.230
And?

28:04.280 --> 28:08.970
They've had some unusual power
outages across the country.

28:08.980 --> 28:13.330
I was told that too much energy demand
was placing a strain on the grid.

28:13.340 --> 28:18.700
Maybe. But what if someone at unr
was purposely shutting off the supply?

28:18.710 --> 28:21.480
The price of energy would go right up.

28:23.640 --> 28:28.600
If walter kendrick is leaking information
about the timing of the shutdown,

28:28.650 --> 28:31.480
an energy trader would know
exactly when to place a bet.

28:31.550 --> 28:34.110
They'd make a fortune.

28:34.820 --> 28:39.100
If kendrick got caught, he'd go to
prison. He-he'd lose the company.

28:40.260 --> 28:42.950
He'd never do it.

28:43.320 --> 28:45.280
It's way too big a risk.

28:45.340 --> 28:49.410
I know how you feel about him.

28:50.000 --> 28:52.350
He has been good to you.

28:52.370 --> 28:56.540
He made your career, but he
is not the man you think he is.

28:57.900 --> 29:01.530
Whatever happened that night in
your house with your wife is over.

29:01.570 --> 29:06.650
It's done with. This
is a partnership now.

29:06.660 --> 29:09.600
You have my word.

29:11.150 --> 29:14.520
What are you talking about?

29:14.530 --> 29:16.880
Aracite is toxic.

29:16.910 --> 29:18.500
The final report said that it was safe.

29:18.520 --> 29:20.440
Kendrick had the report doctored.

29:20.470 --> 29:21.860
Then why'd you testify on his behalf?

29:21.910 --> 29:24.790
Because I cut a deal with him.

29:26.130 --> 29:32.210
If I certified that aracite was harmless,
kendrick promised he would clean it up.

29:34.050 --> 29:37.720
I have nothing to gain
by lying to you, claire.

29:37.730 --> 29:40.450
Ask kendrick...

29:40.500 --> 29:46.890
if aracite is toxic. If he denies
it, you know you can't trust him.

29:57.880 --> 30:00.110
You want another drink?

30:00.140 --> 30:01.870
'Cause I have a minibar.

30:01.900 --> 30:06.440
No, no, no, I-i think-- uh-uh--
I think you have had enough.

30:06.480 --> 30:09.610
No, come on, just one more.

30:09.630 --> 30:13.370
Nope, go to bed. I'm
gonna get you some water.

30:18.790 --> 30:22.030
- Ellen, what is it?
- I'm so sorry.

30:22.040 --> 30:25.900
It's okay, it's, it's
okay. Lay down, sweetie.

30:28.330 --> 30:32.320
I can'T... I can't
talk to anyone, katie.

30:33.060 --> 30:36.700
You can. You can talk to me.

30:36.710 --> 30:39.940
You don't understand.

30:39.950 --> 30:44.630
Ellen, I think you need to
take some time to yourself.

30:45.120 --> 30:46.980
I can'T.

30:47.030 --> 30:50.640
Maybe you shouldn't be
working for patty right now.

30:52.920 --> 30:56.250
I'm not really working for patty.

30:57.960 --> 31:00.670
What?

31:00.710 --> 31:05.910
Ellen, you're drunk. Go to sleep.

31:11.110 --> 31:13.570
I'm sorry I pushed you the other day.

31:13.580 --> 31:15.100
Don't worry about it.

31:15.160 --> 31:19.650
All I care about is being able to
protect the company and protect you.

31:19.700 --> 31:21.580
I get it, claire.

31:23.020 --> 31:26.740
Good, because there's something
else we need to talk about.

31:26.750 --> 31:29.790
- What's that?
- Aracite.

31:29.800 --> 31:35.300
I was looking over the documents that
daniel purcell leaked to patty hewes.

31:35.310 --> 31:36.640
What for?

31:36.670 --> 31:40.270
Well, it always bothered me
that he flipped on the stand.

31:40.280 --> 31:45.740
His original research states

31:45.750 --> 31:48.490
that aracite is highly toxic.

31:49.420 --> 31:52.440
He was wrong and he admitted it.

31:52.450 --> 31:55.840
So there's nothing we
need to worry about.

31:56.980 --> 32:00.710
There's nothing we need to
clean up in west virginia?

32:00.720 --> 32:03.810
I'm telling you aracite is safe.

32:03.820 --> 32:08.640
Okay, because if there's anything in this that
can come back to haunt us ever, I need to know.

32:08.690 --> 32:10.480
No, you don'T.

32:10.530 --> 32:16.460
You just need to do your job and be my
goddamned lawyer and stop asking questions.

32:26.420 --> 32:29.100
What do you think?

32:29.540 --> 32:32.720
It's all right if you hate
it. It's not for everyone.

32:32.730 --> 32:35.330
No, it isn'T.

32:37.500 --> 32:40.340
I appreciate you making
time to come see me.

32:40.370 --> 32:43.950
I, I called because I
felt like we should talk.

32:43.960 --> 32:47.330
- May I ask you a question?
- Sure.

32:47.650 --> 32:51.620
You appear to be an
intelligent, attractive woman.

32:51.650 --> 32:54.480
Why are you dating a child?

32:54.490 --> 32:57.840
We both know that
michael is not a child.

32:57.850 --> 33:00.450
Are you mentally ill?

33:02.170 --> 33:05.090
I really think I understand
what's going on here.

33:05.140 --> 33:07.740
And, uh, it's not about me and michael.

33:07.750 --> 33:09.210
No?

33:09.250 --> 33:12.370
You're facing the
prospect of an empty nest,

33:12.380 --> 33:16.310
so you're clinging to this notion
that michael still needs you.

33:16.360 --> 33:19.890
And, I mean, I can
assure you he doesn'T.

33:22.640 --> 33:25.680
But you'll see--
that's a good thing.

33:28.080 --> 33:30.320
You will break his heart.

33:30.360 --> 33:34.650
And when you do--
I'll rip your face off.

33:37.530 --> 33:40.930
I have to get back to
work, but feel free to stay.

33:40.940 --> 33:46.480
And, uh, if you see anything you like,
I'll give you the family discount.

33:51.890 --> 33:54.360
He lied.

33:55.020 --> 33:59.390
thanks for these. I compared them.

33:59.400 --> 34:02.810
It's clear the final
report was doctored.

34:04.300 --> 34:06.050
I'm sorry, claire.

34:06.060 --> 34:11.179
He told me there was no reason to clean
up aracite, because aracite wasn't toxic.

34:11.190 --> 34:14.080
So he lied to both of us.

34:16.659 --> 34:21.110
I gave half of my life to
this man and his company.

34:21.120 --> 34:23.989
And it turns out he's a criminal.

34:24.000 --> 34:26.870
What are you going to do?

34:27.929 --> 34:31.100
I don't want to think
about it right now.

34:32.330 --> 34:34.770
I miss you.

34:37.909 --> 34:41.449
- You've been drinking.
- What do you care?

34:55.960 --> 34:58.740
I'm heading out.

34:58.750 --> 35:00.450
****

35:03.390 --> 35:05.870
- What?
- I think I want in.

35:05.880 --> 35:07.600
Oh, good.

35:07.620 --> 35:10.120
I'm going to want to
meet this guy first.

35:10.170 --> 35:12.490
I will set that up.

35:13.250 --> 35:15.950
All right.

35:17.390 --> 35:20.010
What, you-you-- you're going
out with the stewardess?

35:20.020 --> 35:21.860
Yeah, don't tell pam.

35:21.870 --> 35:25.660
Oh, shit, I won'T. Have fun, baby!

35:42.760 --> 35:45.220
Can I come in?

36:02.540 --> 36:05.470
That's not good--
you're back already?

36:18.790 --> 36:21.140
You leaving?

36:36.440 --> 36:39.790
- What's wrong?
- I don't know.

36:40.270 --> 36:43.050
I have to tell you something.

36:43.060 --> 36:47.440
The first time we went
to the firing range, I...

36:48.170 --> 36:51.050
I told you something I
probably shouldn't have.

36:51.070 --> 36:53.560
You said someone tried to kill you.

36:53.860 --> 36:58.620
Yeah. It was my boss.

37:00.570 --> 37:03.260
Patty hewes?

37:03.270 --> 37:06.110
I knew...

37:06.130 --> 37:07.530
some things about her.

37:07.560 --> 37:13.420
And she got paranoid and
tried to get rid of me.

37:16.330 --> 37:18.110
That's insane.

37:18.140 --> 37:21.150
Why the hell are you
still working for her?

37:21.750 --> 37:24.410
I'm not.

37:24.420 --> 37:27.080
You lost me.

37:27.090 --> 37:28.530
I'm crazy to be telling you this.

37:28.570 --> 37:32.770
But I just feel like if
I don't talk about it,

37:32.780 --> 37:35.450
- I'm going to lose my mind.
- Tell me.

37:39.730 --> 37:43.290
Five months ago, i was
approached by the fbi.

37:43.830 --> 37:46.430
*******

37:47.170 --> 37:50.090
- Ellen.
- Mr. Nye.

37:50.100 --> 37:52.020
Get in the car.

37:52.030 --> 37:54.140
I'm agent harrison.
This is agent werner.

37:54.150 --> 37:58.080
They said they were investigating
patty hewes, and they...

37:59.140 --> 38:02.010
they asked me to be an informant.

38:02.020 --> 38:04.410
- And-and you
said... - Yes.

38:04.420 --> 38:06.520
Jesus.

38:06.530 --> 38:08.940
Thanks for the chat.

38:14.190 --> 38:17.090
How's that been for you?

38:19.860 --> 38:24.050
You can't imagine the toll it
takes when everyday is a lie.

38:38.660 --> 38:41.420
She met with someone in a limo.

38:43.150 --> 38:44.400
You got it.

38:44.440 --> 38:48.130
No. No, I can'T.

39:06.840 --> 39:08.750
Why is parsons still alive?

39:08.780 --> 39:11.160
Because I found out why she's
been meeting with the feds.

39:11.200 --> 39:13.010
What the hell is she doing?

39:13.080 --> 39:18.310
The fbi is using her as a cooperating
witness against patty hewes.

39:18.320 --> 39:20.940
That's all parsons
cares about right now.

39:20.980 --> 39:23.480
Taking down patty.

39:24.180 --> 39:26.210
Frobisher doesn't need protecting.

39:26.250 --> 39:30.420
This has got nothing to do with
protecting frobisher. You understand?

39:30.840 --> 39:33.930
This is about me.
Parsons knows too much.

39:33.940 --> 39:36.530
You're safe, rick.

39:36.550 --> 39:38.380
You have nothing to worry about.

39:38.420 --> 39:41.670
That's right. I don'T.

39:42.800 --> 39:44.950
'Cause you're going to do it.

39:44.970 --> 39:46.740
Or I call your old lieutenant.

39:46.750 --> 39:48.980
I tell him what I know.

39:49.020 --> 39:52.600
And I send you to prison for life.

40:00.930 --> 40:04.270
********

40:49.520 --> 40:53.120
You killed him, didn't you?

40:53.530 --> 40:57.210
From what I hear, the man was
a drug addict. It's a tragedy.

40:57.220 --> 41:00.410
You didn't have to do that, asshole.

41:00.420 --> 41:02.860
- He was going to play along.
- No.

41:02.870 --> 41:04.190
He was playing you.

41:04.200 --> 41:06.970
That is... that is bullshit,
and you know that's bullshit.

41:07.240 --> 41:09.540
He made a call to the deputy
director of the bureau.

41:09.550 --> 41:11.750
No. No, he wouldn't have done that.

41:11.760 --> 41:15.160
He reported you to the higher-ups.

41:19.640 --> 41:22.350
you don't have to worry.

41:22.380 --> 41:26.060
The deputy director knows i
have an interest in this case.

41:29.730 --> 41:32.590
Is my... my supervisor in on this?

41:32.600 --> 41:36.510
Of course he is. Now,
get me patty hewes.

41:42.840 --> 41:46.410
******

41:50.810 --> 41:54.430
So it seems like you're not going
to tell me the truth after all?

41:55.240 --> 41:58.100
You'd better not screw this shit up.

41:58.110 --> 42:00.290
That's okay.

42:01.630 --> 42:03.780
I lied, too.

